mutant: m016_bloom_size_off_by_one
target: segment/bloom.go
failure-mode: |
  The per-bloom stride in the block-blooms region header is encoded as
  sizeBytes-1, so readers index blooms with the wrong stride and alias into
  neighbouring filter bytes. Models an off-by-one in an index stride.
expected-detection: |
  PREDICTED SURVIVAL: the oracle reads events directly from blocks and never
  queries the bloom filters, so corrupt blooms do not affect reconstruction.
  Documents a known bloom/read-path blind spot.
expected-tier: none
tiers: default,stress

